@startuml sequence-sync

skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 30
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFFCC
skinparam NoteBorderColor #AAAAAA
skinparam SequenceGroupBodyBackgroundColor #F5F5FF

autonumber
actor Client
boundary Gateway
participant "Reservation\nService" as Reservation
database "reservation_db\n(outbox_event)" as DB
queue "Kafka\nreservation-service\n.reservation-created" as KafkaReservation

== 1. Synchronous HTTP Request ==

Client -> Gateway: POST /api/reservations
activate Gateway
Gateway -> Reservation: Create Reservation Request
activate Reservation

Reservation -> DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION\n  1. INSERT reservation (status: CREATED)\n  2. INSERT outbox_event (status: NEW)
DB --> Reservation: OK
Reservation --> Gateway: 201 Created (id, status=CREATED)
deactivate Reservation
Gateway --> Client: HTTP 201 Created
deactivate Gateway

note over Client, KafkaReservation
  Client gets an immediate HTTP response.
  Async processing continues in background.
end note

== 2. Outbox Scheduler (every 5s) ==

Reservation -> DB: SELECT outbox_event WHERE status=NEW
DB --> Reservation: [ReservationCreatedEvent]
Reservation -> KafkaReservation: Publish ReservationCreatedEvent
activate KafkaReservation
Reservation -> DB: UPDATE outbox_event SET status=SENT
KafkaReservation --> Reservation: ack
deactivate KafkaReservation

note over Reservation
  Outbox guarantees at-least-once delivery:
  DB write and Kafka publish are decoupled.
end note

@enduml
